4bj.title: Conjugacy class
4bj.clickbait: In a group, the elements can be partitioned naturally into certain classes.
4bj.text:
Given an element $g$ of a [-3gd] $G$, the conjugacy class of $g$ in $G$ is $\{ x g x^{-1} : x \in G \}$.
It is the collection of elements to which $g$ is conjugate.
